This paper focuses on energy-efficient unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV)-enabled wireless communications, which involves optimization of UAV trajectory and velocities to minimize energy consumption while satisfying latency constraints. This problem is related to networked systems (cs.NI), robotics (cs.RO), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
